# to connect myself as new user by ssh firstly i should make keychain using
# command 'ssh-keygen'. 
# Send public key to user (/.ssh/id_rsa.pub - public key, /.ssh/id_rsa - privat key).
# Create file ~/.ssh/authorized_keys in user directory and put public key in it.
# setup port and other settings in /etc/ssh/sshd_config
# connect to user from client machine using command - ssh username@ip -p (port).

# vns - Virtual Network Computing - it is a system that allows you to use the keyboard and mouse to interact with the graphical user interface on a remote server.

# https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/vnc-ubuntu-16-04-ru
